Key Match Events: Travis Head and David Warner set a powerful opening partnership of 70 runs from just 30 balls
Australia scored a total of 201 runs, with many players hitting sixes
Adam Zampa took 2 wickets with his first ball
Phil Salt and Jos Buttler scored 37 and 42 respectively before being dismissed
England's chase was unsuccessful, needing 50 runs off the last 10 overs
Post-Match Reflections: Australia captain Mitch Marsh praised the team's all-round performance
Jos Buttler acknowledged the strong start by Australia and the disciplined bowling in the middle overs
